Name: pico-rbgkeypad
Version: 0.1.1
Summary: A Python class for controlling the Pimoroni RGB Keypad for the Raspberry Pi Pico.
Home-page: https://github.com/martinohanlon/pico-rbgkeypad
Author: Martin O'Hanlon
Author-email: martin@ohanlonweb.com
License: MIT
Description: A Python class for controlling the [Pimoroni RGB Keypad](https://shop.pimoroni.com/products/pico-rgb-keypad-base) for the [Raspberry Pi Pico](https://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/pico/getting-started/).
        
        Compatible with MicroPython and CircuitPython.
        
        ```python
        keypad = RGBKeypad()
        
        # make all the keys red
        keypad.color = (255, 0, 0)
        
        # turn a key blue when pressed
        while True:
            for key in keypad.keys:
                if key.is_pressed():
                    key.color = (0, 0, 255)
        ```
        
